{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "20", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "08", "M": "35", "S": "36"}}, "news": [{"title": "Goa plans to convert industrial land from lease to freehold", "para": "Goa Industrial Development Corporation is working on reforms for industrial land ownership conversion.  The corporation is also considering easing rules for plot transfers and subdivisions.  These changes align with the Centre's deregulation initiative for industrial land use.  Allottees will pay a freehold premium to extinguish reversionary rights under the new framework.  Proceeds will fund a corpus, with only interest available for operational expenditure.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/goas-bold-move-transitioning-industrial-land-from-leasehold-to-freehold-ownership/132509924?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1422284/132509924.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Submit DLF City demolition and restoration records: HC to Haryana", "para": "The Punjab and Haryana High Court has ordered the state government to submit demolition and restoration details.  This action concerns properties allegedly involved in unauthorized constructions within DLF City.  The court seeks building bylaws to verify compliance with planning regulations.  It aims to protect lawful buildings while addressing violations.  The court also requires property owners to furnish relevant documentation for adjudication.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/punjab-and-haryana-high-court-orders-haryana-government-to-submit-dlf-city-demolition-records/132509892?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-241018/132509892.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Telangana government to launch one lakh Indiramma houses for the poor in CURE on July 20", "para": "The Indiramma housing scheme for low-income groups will launch Monday at the secretariat.  The government plans to construct one lakh multi-storey flats within the core urban region.  Application processes and eligibility criteria will be released by ministers at the event.  This initiative focuses on prime land parcels close to existing poor communities.  Construction of 3.50 lakh houses across rural and urban areas is planned this fiscal.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/telangana-to-unveil-one-lakh-indiramma-houses-for-urban-poor-on-july-20/132505794?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1919777/132505794.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}